node.text: The safe smartwatch for kids is now available for public pre-order! The Gabb Watch is freedom, peace of mind, and connection for kids and parents. Priced right for kids at $99.99, Gabb Affiliates are offering additional 30% discounts on the Gabb Watch during preorders! To find a Gabb Affiliate search our common hashtags, #FirstPhone #SafePhone #GabbWireless. Don’t miss out, pre-order now through July 21! #Gabb #GabbWatch #SafeTechforKids

node.title: Gabb Watch | The Safe Smartwatch for Kids

node.text:
Congratulations to our newest Gabb Ambassador, Ava Johnson! As a level 10 gymnast, Ava works hard every day to push herself to reach her goals. She truly lives beyond the screen with her Gabb Phone, focusing on what she loves to do and not wasting her time with tech. Her passion to inspire other kids to do the same is contagious! We're so excited to have you as a Gabb Ambassador, Ava!

Thank you to our VIP partner @provobeach, @brighamyounguniversity's @cosmo_cougar, and @bloxdesserts for helping us celebrate Ava and all those who support her!

node.title: The Gabb Ambassador Search Winner Announcement

node.text:
At age 15, Samantha Gordon was honored with the NFL’s first ever “Game Changer” award for her stand-out career on the football field. She began playing tackle football with the boys at age 9, and later pioneered the world’s first all-girls tackle football league. Since then, she’s been featured on a Wheaties Box, an NFL commercial, and a Nike commercial shown during the 91st Academy Awards. Do you think she accomplished all that sitting around staring at her phone? No way. Sam wakes up early and trains hard, and that’s what gives her an edge.
.
.
.
@gabblife @docoolstuff @livebeyoundthescreen

node.text:
Children are most commonly exposed to mature content, explicit language, and inappropriate interactions on social media. Some even fall extreme victim to cyberbullies, online perpetrators, and sex crimes. Privacy settings are meant to avoid these kinds of dangers, but even the most basic tech-savvy tween can override certain parental controls on their smartphone. 
The danger: unwanted followers who do not have your child's best interest in mind. The solution: safe tech for kids. Introducing tech in steps can help build your child's maturity and readiness to navigate the digital world safely. #FirstPhone #SafePhone #TechInSteps

node.text:
Parents can never be too careful when it comes to protecting their kids on social media. No matter how much they prepare, today’s parents are faced with tough decisions to ensure the safety of their teens.
If you’re considering allowing your teen/tween a profile on the latest social media platform, here are a few tips to keep them as safe as possible:

1. Hold off until social maturity.
If you feel your child isn’t quite ready to log on to the latest platform, be transparent about the things they can do to prove their growth and maturity to you.

2. Emphasize that social media isn’t reality.
Your kids shouldn’t believe everything they see online. Remind them that everyone only presents the very best versions of themselves on social media: their bodies, hair and makeup, their latest trip to Europe- kids shouldn’t compare their natural selves to an influencer’s filtered life and looks.

3. Forbid interactions with strangers.
Teach your kid the dangers of meeting strangers on the internet and the importance of not sharing any personal information.

4. Give yourself authorized access to the account.
This can help you keep track of your kid’s digital activity and prevent scams, harassment, and cyberbullies. Once your kid has shown that they can act appropriately online, you can limit your access to their accounts.

node.text: @skybrown says it best, less screen time means more skate time! When kids scroll less, they have more time to live life to the fullest and do cool stuff. Living beyond the screen means learning to balance tech appropriately to accomplish amazing things. Who better to show us how it's done than self-taught 12-year-old skateboarder, Sky Brown! We're excited to have Sky on board to help us empower kids to live beyond the screen and make their dreams a reality. #Gabb #LiveBeyondTheScreen #DoCoolStuff #Skateboarding

node.text:
The Gabb Watch makes messaging easy! Simply set up to 10 custom contacts to ensure safe, exclusive communication-no outside texts or calls. The built-in microphone allows for easy voice messaging directly to their contacts. The pre-set text message feature makes for quick responses and can be customized for your kid’s needs. The watch even includes emojis to make messages more fun! ⁠
Pre-ordering is open now through July 21! Use promo code WATCH30 for 30% off the device! #GabbWatch #SafeTechForKids

node.text: Having a collection is something kids can be proud of. Kids can collect from experiences, vacations, hobbies, and more! Encourage your kids to make ordinary things special by creating collections out of them! Share your ideas on what kids can collect below! #UnpluggedActivity

node.text: Allowing your child access to social media too early means exposing them to the dangers and complications of social media before they are ready. Starting kids off with safe check-in steps, paired with ongoing digital safety education, will set kids up to become tech-savvy adults. Visit our blog page to learn more about parenting in a hyper-tech world. #FirstPhone #SafePhone
